<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Arraign" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Arraign,</orth> to summon before a court of justice: <cit><quote>I'll teach you how you shall a. your conscience,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.3.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 3, 21</bibl></cit>. In general, to accuse: <bibl n="shak. wt 2.3.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. II, 3, 202</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.5.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 5, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 22</bibl> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.4.152" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 4, 152</bibl>. <cit><quote>accused and --ed of high treason,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 2, 14</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>who can a. me for't?</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.159" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 159</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>